&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The bolded portion just makes no sense to me, especially when mobs hit for full damage. Do you Dev types even play the game anymore? Are you oblivious to the waining population of healers? The days of 10+ clerics are long gone. Most guilds are using bare minimum of healers and even then we have to be super&amp;nbsp;slick on how to squeeze the needed healing power out of our small healer force.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;AE Rampage should NEVER hit for full damage UNLESS it's avoidable by paying attention and staying out of its range, otherwise you are giving a big FU to pure melee because most guilds cannot afford the healing resources to allow them to get in and melee. Not to mention its a huge risk anyways if a mob can one round them. Guilds will go to ranged strats and&amp;nbsp;pure melee&amp;nbsp;will have to sit back and throw stuff for 10pts a pop. Gogo l33t dps.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I can't believe you even intended this in the first place. This is inherently bad for EQ in general.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;U&gt;AE rampage should be a mechanism to either:&lt;/U&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;A) Add a SMALL amount of extra healing to an encounter by having AE rampage that hits for low amounts.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;(This would be that unavoidable type)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;OR&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;B) Be avoidable&amp;nbsp;by meleeing at max range. Reward for paying attention, punishment for not.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;BOTH scenarios allow melee to participate in the fight. Which is obviously good for EQ as a whole. I&amp;nbsp;guess I can't wrap my head around the thinking process of designers of a game that is based upon grouping and class balance creating events that exclude people on a large scale.&amp;nbsp;Full damage, unavoidable AE Rampage does just that and its very very wrong.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Dev's, please look at the game from a players perspective. We are not asking for encounters to be made easier. We are asking that you do not include mechanics that make certain classes useless in raids. If AE rampage is going to remain full damage and unavoidable I can see alot of pissed off pure melee. I personally would like to know if this trend will continue, if so I will be recruiting more ranged classes.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
