      <title>Re: AE rampage Since last patch</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&amp;message.id=253660#M253660</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;You need to realize that when I say how AE rampage works, I'm just telling you how it was built to work many, many years ago, not how I would make it work if I were making it today.&amp;nbsp; I happen to agree with many of your points, but that's not how it was built.&amp;nbsp; AE rampage was built to do a mobs full hit to everyone who can hit the NPC.&amp;nbsp; There's&amp;nbsp;an error somewhere in there that makes it not work that way on certain NPCs.&amp;nbsp; Since I have no intention of changing that, I've never bothered to go figure out what the error is.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Later, the ability to scale rampage damage was added, which also lowers AE ramage damage.&amp;nbsp; Unfortunately, since they were&amp;nbsp;tied together, we&amp;nbsp;can't tune down one without lowering the other.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;We've just added a seperate tuning mechanism for AE rampage that lets us&amp;nbsp;set that damage seperately from rampage so we can tone down AE rampage damage without affecting rampage damage...something I hope to do on older NPCs in the near future.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Rashere&lt;/P&gt;</description>
