    <item>
      <title>Re: AE rampage Since last patch</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&amp;message.id=244964#M244964</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
Yitamin wrote:&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;Rashere or Prathun, can you guys confirm what you mean by fixed, please? Do you mean those zones and scripts were returned to their state prior to the mob abilities fix? In particular it seems like a lot of encounters that had only one type of rampage, either single or AE, ended up with both. In addition it seems like the actual damage amount on one or both of those was also affected, most notable when it increased significantly. Will these encounters that have been noted as being fixed behave as they did prior to the abilities fix, or do they just have one of the rampages disabled? I'm just trying to get a solid handle on what we can trust to be similar to what we know, and what we should be prepared to go into full force, expecting the worst. &lt;SPAN&gt;:smileyhappy:&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;It varies depending on the needs of the event.&amp;nbsp; For most events, we tried to return it to what was happening before the patch, which generally meant removing AE rampage entirely.&amp;nbsp; Sendaii and the Anguish events are a good example.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;In others, like Co9, the chance to AE rampage was greatly reduced, but not removed entirely&amp;nbsp;(in this particular case, it was lowered from 30% to 1% chance).&amp;nbsp; In others, they still AE ramage, but for much less damage than before (Txevu and Tacvi mobs are good examples).&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The safest bet is to be careful with events we've changed and feel them out again on your next attempt before you just engage with your old patterns.&amp;nbsp; While most of them should be back to their old behavior, some will react a bit differently and may require slightly different tactics.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Rashere&lt;/P&gt;</description>
